-- Evans Gives U.S. 2-1 Win Over Jamaica in World Cup Qualifier
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-06-08T04:50:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-08/evans-gives-u-s-2-1-win-over-jamaica-in-world-cup-qualifier.html
Brad Evans scored in the second
minute of stoppage time to give the U.S. a 2-1 victory at
 Jamaica  in a World Cup soccer qualifier.  Jozy Altidore scored in the 30th minute as the Americans
took a 1-0 lead. Jermaine Beckford tied the game off a free kick
in the 89th minute at Independence Park in Kingston, Jamaica.  The U.S. (2-1-1) improved to seven points in the 10-game
final round of the North and Central American and Caribbean
region. The Americans trail Costa Rica (2-1-1) on goal
difference and are ahead of Mexico (1-0-4) on goals scored.  The Americans host Panama on June 11 in Seattle and
Honduras on June 18 at Sandy,  Utah .  The top three nations qualify for next yearâ€™s 32-nation
World Cup tournament in  Brazil , and the No. 4 team meets New
Zealand in a playoff for another berth.  To contact the reporter on this story:
